Please choose an option from the menu.

options.description: Step-by-step commands to run your app

parts.text:
Great ‚Äî here are the local setup steps.

Python Setup (Path B)
- Init: mv .env.template .env
- Venv: python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
- Deps: pip install -r requirements.txt
- Run: python app.py (Default port: 8000)
- Import: python common/repository/cyoda/cyoda_init.py

Java Setup (Path A)
- Init: Rename .env.template to .env
- Config: Update CYODA_HOST and ensure ENTITY_VERSION is unique
- Import: ./gradlew importWorkflows
- Run: Test at http://localhost:8080

Need anything else ‚Äî e.g., help with one of these commands, troubleshooting an error, or do you want me to check your cloud environment or generate credentials/resources? (If you ask to check env or generate credentials/resources I‚Äôll hand that off to the appropriate agent.)
